ce:section.ce:para:
As we know, purification process greatly affects the fluorescent property and subsequent application of CDs. Precipitation method has been reported to purify LWE-CDs in the last two years [44,45]. Compared with the most commonly used methods, such as column chromatography and dialysis, precipitation method is simpler, quicker and cheaper [31–38]. The key of precipitation method is to select a suitable precipitant. Many solvents were tried in our experiment, but PEI-CDs could not be precipitated. Considering the fact that PEI-CDs were prepared in water, which is a strongest polar solvent, ethanol was added to decrease the polarity of the mixture. After that, petroleum ether was employed to precipitate PEI-CDs. In this way, the precipitates of PEI-CDs were obtained. However, PLQY of PEI-CDs was very low (Table 1
                        ). Further studies demonstrated that this was due to the existence of the unreacted raw materials, i.e. TAB and PEI. To solve the problem, the mixture after reaction were subjected to dialysis against ultrapure water for 6 h before the precipitation process. Fortunately, good results were achieved. After the precipitates were washed and dried, brownish-black solid particles were obtained (Fig. 1
                        ). The productive yield (PY) was 14.6%. PEI-CDs were very easy to dissolve in water, and the PLQY of the aqueous solution was tested to be 21.9% (Table 1), which is four times higher than that of PEI-CDs purified by the precipitation method. Moreover, the PLQYs of most of the reported LWE-CDs are around 10% [29–31,37,38,44,46]. So, it can be concluded that LWE-PEI-CDs purified by dialysis-precipitation method have higher fluorescence emission efficiency. In order to further verify the superiority of the proposed dialysis-precipitation method, dialysis method was also employed to purify PEI-CDs. The results are demonstrated in Table 1. It can be seen that the PY of the dialysis-precipitation method is as 5 time as much as that of the dialysis method, and the PLQY of PEI-CDs purified by the dialysis-precipitation way is much higher than that purified by the dialysis way. And the dialysis time was also reduced by 75%.
